By Esther Egbe

Former Enyimba player and Al Nassr winger Daniel Etor was robbed in his Abuja home recently, and the resulting trauma has left his wife  and left his wife hospitalised.

National Daily learnt that the robbers broke into the Apo home of Etor  on Monday night and carted away valuables worth millions of Naira.

ALSO READ: European powers insist on Iran nuclear deal

The robbers reportedly demanded huge sums of cash from Etor’s wife. She, however, couldn’t come up with it.

Etor was named best foreign player in Oman last year.

His club Al Nassr are second on the league table with four rounds of matches till the end of the season.

			
